headline: Why Bank Stocks JPMorgan Chase, Bank of America, and Wells Fargo Are Falling Ahead of Earnings
summary: After a rip-roaring rally yesterday, stocks resumed their sell-off today, as unrest about tariffs and U.S.-Chinese relations once again found the spotlight.  Shares of JPMorgan Chase (NYSE: JPM) traded roughly 4% lower.  Shares of Bank of America (NYSE: BAC) and Wells Fargo (NYSE: WFC) had fallen roughly 4.6% and 5.7%, respectively.
